/************************************************ JAVA *************************************/

Optimal Approach - we are using a stack to solve this problem. Basically, we use a stack as an open and closed parentheses verifier. 

class Solution {
    public boolean isValid(String s) {
        // Stack to store expected closing brackets
        Stack<Character> st = new Stack<>();
        // Iterate through each character in the string
        for (char ch : s.toCharArray()) {
            // If opening bracket, push its corresponding closing bracket
            if (ch == '(') {
                st.push(')');
            }
            else if (ch == '{') {
                st.push('}');
            }
            else if (ch == '[') {
                st.push(']');
            }
            // If closing bracket
            else {
                // If stack is empty OR top of stack doesn't match
                // current closing bracket â†’ invalid
                if (st.isEmpty() || st.pop() != ch)
                    return false;
            }
        }
        // Stack should be empty if all brackets matched correctly
        return st.isEmpty();
    }
}
Time Complexity :- O(N)
Space Complexity :- O(N)
